.TH meta 3
.SH NAME
\*Lmeta\*O \- Forces the number of significant bits on input
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lmeta(\*Vwin\*L, \*Vbf\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L;
    bool \*Vbf\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "meta subroutine"
This function forces the user's terminal to return 7 or 8
significant bits on input.  To force 8 bits to be returned,
invoke \*Lmeta\*O with \*Lbf\*O as \*LTRUE\*O.
To force 7 bits to be returned, invoke \*Lmeta\*O with \*Lbf\*O
as \*LFALSE\*O.
.PP
The window argument is always ignored, but it must still be
a valid window to avoid compiler errors.
.EQ
